    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-11T10:06:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="186"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3626: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1919-01-11T23:06:00+08:00"
                            notBefore="1919-01-10T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 11, 1919, 11:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from [<persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName> at] Omsk.</p>
                <p>“14. 10th. <persName corresp="#p_GGGR1">General Gaida</persName> informed me
                    today that he has resigned his command of the Czech troops and joined the
                    Siberian Army as Lieutenant General. He, together with <persName
                        corresp="#p_PGAN1">General Pepelyaev</persName>, will have charge of the
                    operations on the western front. The plan is to concentrate troops in the
                    direction of Viake [<hi rend="italic">Viatka?</hi>] and Vologda in an attempt to
                    reach Moscow by spring. <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">Harris</persName>.[”]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RPS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
